==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ang}} ''[[cyrin|ċyrin]]''. Cognate with West Frisian {{term|tsjerne}} and Dutch {{term|karnen}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{enPR|chû(r)n}}, {{IPA|/tʃɜː(r)n/}}, {{SAMPA|/tS3:(r)n/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/tʃɚn/}}, {{SAMPA|/tS@`n/}}
* {{audio|en-us-churn.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɜː(r)n}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{transitive}} To [[agitate]] [[rapid]]ly and [[repetitive]]ly, or to [[stir]] with a [[row]]ing or [[rock]]ing motion; generally applies to [[liquid]]s, notably [[cream]].
#: ''Now the cream is '''churned''' to make butter.''
# {{context|transitive|figuratively}} To [[produce]] [[excessive]] and sometimes [[undesirable]] or [[unproductive]] [[activity]] or [[motion]].
# {{intransitive}} To move rapidly and repetitively with a rocking motion; to [[tumble]], [[mix]] or [[shake]].
#: ''I was so nervous my stomach was '''churning'''.''

